# project

- label: all tests pass
  command: npm test

# package
- label: package name is
  command: grep -q '"name": "@avcodes/mi"' package.json
  tags: [avcodes/mi]
- label: ESM module (type: module in package.json)
  command: grep -q '"type": "module"' package.json
- label: bin entry maps 'mi' to ./index.mjs
  command: node -e "const p=JSON.parse(require('fs').readFileSync('package.json'));process.exit(p.bin?.mi==='./index.mjs'?0:1)"
- label: zero npm dependencies — Node builtins and native fetch only
  command: node -e "const p=JSON.parse(require('fs').readFileSync('package.json'));process.exit(p.dependencies?1:0)"
- label: published files are index.mjs, tools/, and skills/ only
  command: node -e "const p=JSON.parse(require('fs').readFileSync('package.json'));const f=p.files;process.exit(f.length===3&&f.includes('index.mjs')&&f.includes('tools')&&f.includes('skills')?0:1)"
- label: MIT license
  command: grep -q '"license": "MIT"' package.json

# architecture
- core logic lives in index.mjs — every non-shebang line is intentionally dense
- label: tools hot-load from tools/*.mjs via dynamic import before each model call
  command: grep -q 'await loadTools(); const response' index.mjs
- tool modules default-export { name, description, parameters, handler }
- label: skills are markdown playbooks in skills/<name>/SKILL.md with YAML frontmatter
  command: test -f skills/debug/SKILL.md && head -1 skills/debug/SKILL.md | grep -q '^---'
- skills loaded from two search paths: bundled (MI_DIR/skills/) then user (~/.agents/skills/)
- label: no build step, no transpilation, no lint config
  command: ! test -f tsconfig.json && ! test -f .eslintrc.json && ! test -f webpack.config.js
- Node builtins exposed globally for tool modules: spawn, readFileSync, existsSync, readdirSync, homedir

# tools
- label: exactly two tools: bash (shell execution) and skill (skill discovery/loading)
  command: test $(ls tools/*.mjs | wc -l) -eq 2 && test -f tools/bash.mjs && test -f tools/skill.mjs
- label: bash tool runs commands in detached process groups for clean signal handling
  command: grep -q 'detached.*true' tools/bash.mjs
- label: bash tool supports timeout (ms) and background (bg) modes
  command: grep -q 'timeout' tools/bash.mjs && grep -q 'bg' tools/bash.mjs
- label: background bash writes output to /tmp/mi-{timestamp}.log, returns pid and log path
  command: grep -q '/tmp/mi-' tools/bash.mjs
- skill tool without name lists all available skills; with name returns SKILL.md body
- label: skill frontmatter parsed via regex (^name: and ^description: with multiline flag)
  command: grep -q '/m' tools/skill.mjs

# agent-loop
- agent loop streams OpenAI chat completions via SSE, executes tool calls, repeats until text response
- SSE parser buffers incomplete frames, splits on double-newline, skips [DONE] and malformed JSON
- tool call fragments streamed by index — id/type overwrite, name/arguments append
- label: tool output logged truncated to 200 chars; full result sent to model
  command: grep -q '200' index.mjs
- unknown tool calls return error listing available tools instead of crashing

# cli
- four CLI modes: interactive REPL, one-shot (-p), stdin pipe, and file context (-f)
- /reset command splices history to keep only system prompt
- REPL error recovery pops failed user message so model never sees it
- version banner prints '◰ mi/<version>' in orange and gray ANSI
- label: ANSI color helpers: gray (90), red (31), orange (38;5;208)
  command: grep -q '208' index.mjs

# system-prompt
- system prompt = SYSTEM_PROMPT env (full override) or built-in DEFAULT_PROMPT
- label: default prompt enforces terse raw-terminal transcript persona
  command: grep -q 'quiet, mechanical, precise' index.mjs && grep -q 'at most one status line under 8 words' index.mjs
- system message appends: CWD, ISO date, -f file content, AGENTS.md (if present), skill summaries
- label: AGENTS.md auto-ingested from CWD and appended to system prompt
  command: grep -q 'AGENTS.md' index.mjs

# env
- label: default model is gpt-5.4 (MODEL env var)
  command: grep -q 'gpt-5.4' index.mjs
- label: default API base is https://api.openai.com (OPENAI_BASE_URL env var)
  command: grep -q 'api.openai.com' index.mjs
- OPENAI_API_KEY required for all modes except -h
- label: REASONING_EFFORT is optional and omitted from API requests when unset
  command: grep -q 'reasoning_effort.*REASONING_EFFORT' index.mjs
- MI_DIR and MI_PATH set in process.env for tools/skills to locate package assets

# skills
- label: 11 bundled skills: debug, delegate, explore, new-skill, plan, refactor, review, self, tasks, tdd, verify
  command: test $(ls -d skills/*/SKILL.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l) -eq 11
- label: user skills live in ~/.agents/skills/ and are merged with bundled skills
  command: test -d skills/debug

# testing
- label: test suite uses node --test with mocked OpenAI-compatible HTTP server
  command: grep -q 'node --test' package.json
- tests cover: CLI modes, SSE streaming, tool calls, tool hot-loading, REPL reset, error recovery, SIGINT, AGENTS.md, skills, Unicode
- label: npm run lines counts meaningful LOC in index.mjs and tools/*.mjs — target is 30 total
  command: grep -q 'count-lines' package.json
- label: count-lines.mjs is language-aware: strips comments and blank lines for JS, Python, and Shell
  command: test -f scripts/count-lines.mjs
- label: auxiliary tests: test_exit.js (exit codes) and test_sigint.cjs (signal handling) — not in npm test
  command: test -f tests/test_exit.js && test -f tests/test_sigint.cjs

# publishing
- label: publishing triggered by GitHub Release or workflow_dispatch
  command: test -f .github/workflows/publish.yml
- label: uses OIDC tokenless publish with provenance — no NPM_TOKEN secret
  command: grep -q 'provenance' .github/workflows/publish.yml
- label: CI requires Node 24.x
  command: grep -q '24' .github/workflows/publish.yml

# harbor
- label: mi_harbor/ is a Python adapter for running mi against Harbor benchmarks (Terminal-Bench 2.0)
  command: test -f mi_harbor/mi_agent.py
- harbor adapter includes diagnostic instrumentation: pre-flight LLM check, timestamped output, network diagnostics
- label: harbor is dev/eval infrastructure only — excluded from npm package
  command: grep -q 'mi_harbor' .npmignore
